The problem with my previous answer was that the method forEach just loops over all of them but during the looping process the index's were being removed from the array so it could end up removing the wrong index, this new solution takes into account the removing of indexs.

    for(var i = 0; i < $scope.list.length; i++) {
     if($scope.list[i].done)  {
      $scope.list.splice(index, 1);
      i--;
     };
    };

