I'm not sure what's the best solution here, but one thing I know (that did work) was to use Node.js built-in module `http` instead of requiring express module. ```var http = require('http');

http.createServer(function (req, res) {
    res.writeHead(200, {'Content-Type': 'text/plain'});
    res.send('it is running\n');
}).listen(process.env.PORT || 5000); ```

